properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 6:29PM HST until February 10 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH WIND WARNING THROUGH 6 AM TUESDAY FOR THE BIG ISLAND
SUMMITS...
...HIGH WIND WARNING FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM MONDAY FOR
HALEAKALA SUMMIT...
...WIND ADVISORY THROUGH 6 PM MONDAY FOR NIIHAU KAUAI AND OAHU...
...WIND ADVISORY FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT THROUGH 6 ON MONDAY FOR
REMAINDER OF MAUI COUNTY AND THE BIG ISLAND...

* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with localized gusts over 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Portions of Kahoolawe, Lanai, Maui, Molokai and the
lower elevations of the Big Island, with the strongest winds
near mountains, gaps and where winds blow downslope from higher
terrain..

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 6 PM HST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Winds this strong are capable of downing tents or
other temporary structures, as well as downing trees and causing
power outages.
properties.instruction:
Motorists should use extra caution.

Secure trash cans, lawn furniture, and other loose outdoor
objects that can be easily blown around by strong winds.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM HST MONDAY
